  "text": "Various surrogates have been adopted to accelerate the Bayesian inference for inverse problems [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . For example, the Gaussian process regression (GPR) or Kriging model was used in [CITATION_5] to approximate the relation between parameters and the forward solutions. In [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] , the generalized polynomial chaos (gPC) expansion was employed to approximate the forward solution of the PDE models as a function of the random parameters in the Karhunen-Loéve (KL) expansion of the unknown coefficient.",
